  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Container With Most Water\n\nGiven vertical line heights, choose two lines that together with the x-axis hold the largest possible area.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: height = [1, 8, 6, 2, 5, 4, 8, 3, 7]\nOutput: 49\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: height = [5, 5]\nOutput: 5\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: height = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\nOutput: 6\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- `2 <= len(height) <= 100000`\n- `0 <= height[i] <= 10000`",
  "editorial": "The area is limited by the shorter side. Start wide, then move the pointer at the shorter side because keeping it cannot improve future areas.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def maxArea(self, height):\n        left, right = 0, len(height) - 1\n        best = 0\n        while left < right:\n            best = max(best, min(height[left], height[right]) * (right - left))\n            if height[left] < height[right]:\n                left += 1\n            else:\n                right -= 1\n        return best\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Width shrinks every move, so the only possible improvement is a taller limiting wall.",
    "Move away from the shorter side."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def maxArea(self, height):\n        pass\n"
  },
